Brute Force Approach
- Check every possible pair of numbers and see if their sum equals the target.
- code :-

class Solution:
    def twoSum(self, nums, target):
        n = len(nums)

        for i in range(n):
            for j in range(i + 1, n):
                if nums[i] + nums[j] == target:
                    return [i, j]


Optimized Approach
- Instead of searching for the second number every time, store already visited numbers in a hashmap.
- code:-

class Solution:
    def twoSum(self, nums, target):
        seen = {}  # dictionary to store number: index
        for i, num in enumerate(nums):
            diff = target - num
            if diff in seen:
                return [seen[diff], i]
            seen[num] = i
